<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BOOKS WANTED FOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city of Compton is asking people to donate books that will be given to high 
school students in early January in commemoration of Martin Luther King Jr.'s 
birthday on Jan. 15. 
</P>
<P>
Books may be dropped off at the lobby of Compton's City Hall at 205 S. 
Willowbrook Ave. through next Friday. They will be distributed to students from 
Jan. 8 to Jan. 15. All kinds of books, especially those about King and 
African-American history and literature, are welcome. 
</P>
</TEXT>
