</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA: IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
W. LEONARD ELECTED CHAIRMAN OF CTC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Transportation Commission announced the election of William E. 
Leonard of San Bernardino as chairman for 1990. Leonard, owner of the Leonard 
Realty and Building Co., was appointed to the commission in 1985 by Gov. George 
Deukmejian, and to a second term that will expire in February, 1993. He had 
already been a member from 1973 to 1977, including one year as chairman. 
Elected vice chairman for 1990 was Bruce Nestande, a former legislator who is 
vice president of the Arnel Development Co. of Costa Mesa. He was an Orange 
County supervisor from 1981 to 1987. 
</P>
