<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: EAST COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Firefighters found the body of an elderly woman while battling a fire at her 
home east of El Cajon early Thursday, the San Diego County Sheriff's Department 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The burned body of Ann Mercurio, 79, was found lying on the floor in a hallway 
of her home on Shadow Knolls Drive, said Deputy Coroner Bob Engel. An autopsy 
will be performed today, he said. 
</P>
<P>
A newspaper carrier on his route reported the fire about 3:43 a.m., a sheriff's 
spokeswoman said. Firefighters from El Cajon, Santee and San Miguel contained 
the blaze, which started in the bedroom, in 25 minutes, she said. 
</P>
<P>
Heat and smoke damage to the wood house and its contents was estimated at 
$75,000, the spokeswoman said. Sheriff's arson detectives are investigating to 
determine the cause of the fire. 
</P>
