<P>
PANAMA EFFECT: The fall of Manuel A. Noriega (A1) may affect one aspect of the 
local drug scene: money-laundering. . . . Strict Panamanian banking laws have 
made it difficult to "track down the paper trail" of drug money, one federal 
agent says. . . . While difficult to pinpoint the dollar amount of the 
O.C.-Panama connection, the agent says, "rest assured, money from Orange County 
dope sales is going through Panama." Mark I. Pinsky 
