<TEXT>
<P>
Gene Altamirano had 22 points to lead Rancho Santiago College to a 72-61 
victory over Mt. San Antonio Thursday in a championship semifinal-round game of 
the Rancho Santiago Holiday basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Altamirano, a sophomore forward, made six of six three-pointers and four of 
four free throws. He scored eight consecutive points to help Rancho Santiago 
overcome Mt. San Antonio in the second half. The Mounties led at the half, 
29-28. 
</P>
<P>
