<HEADLINE>
<P>
OOPS; 
</P>
<P>
TAPE TRAPS DRUG DEALING TEEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DANVILLE, Ind. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A father hoping to surprise his children with a tape recorder for Christmas got 
a surprise of his own -- the device contained a tape of conversations involving 
drug dealing. 
</P>
<P>
An Indianapolis man purchased the recorder at a Wal-Mart store on Dec. 23, 
Sheriff's Department spokesman Lt. Stephen G. Golden said. 
</P>
<P>
The man noticed the tape inside the player, listened to it and turned it over 
to authorities. 
</P>
<P>
The tape was made secretly by parents of a teen-ager who suspected their 
daughter was dealing drugs, Golden said. The parents used a phone answering 
tape device. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators believe the girl learned of the recording and took the tape to 
the store to play, leaving it in a display model, Golden said. 
</P>
<P>
When the recorder was the only one left, employees boxed it and sold it to the 
Indianapolis man. 
</P>
</TEXT>
