<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
UECKER BACK TO PITCH WISCONSIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MADISON, Wis. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sportsman and actor Bob Uecker will be the head pitchman in Wisconsin's annual 
effort to attract spring and summer tourism. 
</P>
<P>
The former Milwaukee Braves baseball player -- better known for his appearances 
in commercials -- agreed to donate his services to the 1990 campaign, as he has 
in the past, officials announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
One of the advertising agencies involved in the project suggested dumping 
Uecker this year, but the state Tourism Council, mindful of the success of 
previous campaigns, decided to use him again. 
</P>
<P>
"Record responses for Wisconsin tourism information came as the result of past 
Uecker spots," said Richard Matty, administrator of the state Division of 
Tourism Development. 
</P>
<P>
Uecker broadcasts Milwaukee Brewers games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
